<li>1918 Popular Science article on various imagined and suggested helicopter design concepts - <i>Flights -- of the Imagination: airships that soar only in the day-dreams of their inventors</i>, <a href="/wiki/Popular_Science" title="Popular Science">Popular Science</a> monthly, December 1918, page 58-59, Scanned by Google Books: <a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=EikDAAAAMBAJ&amp;pg=PA58" class="external free" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=EikDAAAAMBAJ&amp;pg=PA58" rel="nofollow">http://books.google.com/books?id=EikDAAAAMBAJ&amp;pg=PA58</a></li>
</ul>
